text:
Heupel doesn't have the killer instinct. When it comes down to the wire, he always goes conservative and it almost always comes back to bite us. And then when the smart play is to go ahead and kick a field goal with only 7 seconds left on the clock, he makes the risky call to try to one more play -- and ends up costing us 5 yards on an offsides and possibly the score that would have won the game. Then, after the penalty we have to call a timeout and essentially ice our own kicker. 

That being said, today was the best play calling I have seen in a Heupel game, pretty much, well, ever...right up until the point where the calls really mattered.
